  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Flash Beetle",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png",
            "name": "Treasure and Rewards",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Light Glands",
          "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
          "sidebar_type": "treasure_and_rewards",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "1.1",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "1.1",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 42",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core pg. 42",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core",
              "page": 42,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Beetles do not collect treasure, but the two light-producing organs of a flash beetle can be recovered from the creature and used for illumination-based chemical recipes, spell components, and magic item creation.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "errata": {
            "alt": "1.1",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "1.1",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core pg. 42",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core pg. 42",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core",
          "page": 42,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "These 3-foot-long insects boast a pair of glowing organs on the back of the abdomen that give off bright light and that continue to glow for days, even after the creature's death. Flash beetles are commonly herded and harvested by miners and spelunkers, as their glow is considered safer than torches and less expensive than lamps. Denizens of the Darklands often domesticate and train these insects, using them as pets, livestock, or caging them to use as organic sources of light in areas frequented by visitors unaccustomed to the darkness.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
